        "body": "### Error Message and Logs\n\nEnvironment variables marked “Available at Buildtime” do not persist in Coolify v4.0.0-beta.450.\n\n- UI shows checkbox checked\n- “Update” shows success\n- After refresh, still checked\n\nBut:\n\n- Database never updates is_build_time\n- CLI always shows is_build_time: false\n- Build stage never receives React build-time vars (like REACT_APP_*)\n- React builds fail with missing API keys\n\n### Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Go to Application → Environment Variables\n2. Create var (e.g., REACT_APP_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY)\n3. Enable Available at Buildtime\n4. Enable Is Literal\n5. Disable Available at Runtime\n6. Click “Update”\n7. Run CLI:\n`coolify applications env list <app-id> --format table`\n8. Observe: Column 4 (is_build_time) always false\n\n\n\n### Example Repository URL\n\n_No response_\n\n### Coolify Version\n\nv4.0.0-beta.450\n\n### Are you using Coolify Cloud?\n\nNo (self-hosted)\n\n### Operating System and Version (self-hosted)\n\nUbuntu 24.04.3 LTS\n\n### Additional Information\n\n### Actual Behavior\n- Backend ignores the is_build_time value\n- The database never updates the flag\n- CLI always reports is_build_time as false\n- Build environment variables are missing during Docker/Nixpacks build\n- React applications fail with \"Invalid API key\" or missing REACT_APP_* variables\n\n### Expected Behavior\n- The database should correctly save the is_build_time flag\n- CLI should reflect the correct value (true)\n- Docker/Nixpacks build should receive build-time variables reliably\n\n### Workarounds Tried\n- Upgraded to the latest Coolify version (v4.0.0-beta.450)\n- Deleted & recreated environment variables\n- Toggled Developer View / Normal View\n- Switched from Nixpacks to Dockerfile build pack\n- Added ARG/ENV manually in Dockerfile\n- Restarted Coolify and host machine\n\n**None of the workarounds resolved the issue.**\n\n### Impact\nThis prevents React and Next.js apps from building correctly, since REACT_APP_* environment variables are missing at build time. This breaks the deployment workflow entirely.\n",
